    "faq": {
      "type": "faq",
      "blocks": {
        "faq_1": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How does the Aira nasal strip work?",
            "answer": "<p>Aira uses a lightweight magnetic band that gently opens your nasal passages from the outside. Two small adhesive tabs sit on either side of your nose, and the magnetic bridge connects them - creating a soft, outward pull that widens your airway instantly. <br/>No drugs, no intrusion, no discomfort. Just cleaner, more confortable breathing from the moment you put it on.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_2": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Is it comfortable to sleep with and what if it falls off during the night?",
            "answer": "<p>Most people forget they're wearing it within minutes. The strip weighs <strong>less than 2 grams</strong>, sits gently on the outside of your nose, and leaves no residue when you take it off in the morning. </p><p>The adhesive tabs are <strong>medical-grade </strong>and designed to stay put all night - even if you move around in your sleep. On the rare occasion one shifts, it simply means your skin needs to be a little drier or cleaner before application. Your <em>Aira Kit </em>includes a simple application guide to help you get it right from night one.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_3": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How long does the band last?",
            "answer": "<p>The magnetic band is reusable and built to last for months. You only need to replace the adhesive tabs, which come in <strong>packs of 30, 60, or 90 pairs</strong>. One tab lasts for a single use (one night). Unlike single-use strips, Aira was built to last.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_4": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Will it help with my snoring?",
            "answer": "<p>When your nasal passages are open, your body naturally breathes through your nose rather than your mouth, and it's that shift that reduces the soft-tissue vibration behind most snoring problems. Our customers regularly tell us their partners noticed the difference before they did. That says more than any number could!</p>"
          }
        },
        "question_EeFcrc": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How is Aira different from regular adhesive nasal strips?",
            "answer": "<p>Traditional disposable nasal strips rely entirely on adhesive to pull your nose open, which means they weaken as the night goes on, often peel at the edges, and can<strong> irritate sensitive skin.</strong> Aira works differently. The magnetic band does the structural work of keeping your airway open, while the tabs maintain it in place. The result is a stronger, more consistent opening that lasts all night and a gentler experience for your skin. </p>"
          }
        },
        "question_LR3ReA": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "How do I know which size is right for me?",
            "answer": "<p>We've made finding your size easy. The Aira Kit includes four bands sizes: <strong>S2, M1, M2, and L1,</strong> so you can find your perfect fit from the start. A simple way to check: the band should sit with its ends resting gently on the outer edges of your nostrils, without pinching or pressing them closed. Some people also use different sizes depending on the moment, a slightly larger band during exercise for maximum airflow, and a more fitted size for sleep. </p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_5": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Can I use it during exercise?",
            "answer": "<p>Absolutely, and honestly, this is where Aira shines best The adhesive tabs are sweat-resistant and engineered to stay in place through high-intensity workouts, runs, cycling sessions, or even pilates. Nasal breathing during exercise helps regulate your heart rate, improve oxygen uptake, and reduce breathlessness. Whether you're training or winding down, Aira works with your body, not against it.</p>"
          }
        },
        "faq_6": {
          "type": "question",
          "settings": {
            "question": "Do you ship to the GCC?",
            "answer": "<p>Yes, we ship across the GCC, including the UAE, Saudi Arabia, Kuwait, Bahrain, Qatar, and Oman. Most orders arrive within 3–5 business days, and free shipping is available above a certain order value. We're extremely proud to be part of the wellness journey of customers across the region.</p>"
          }
        }
      },
